The paper discusses the quality of graph visualizations, which is a topic that falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and graph theory (cs.GR). The paper also discusses visualization techniques such as multidimensional scaling (cs.CV), edge bundling (cs.SI), and visualization metaphors (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.HC and cs.GR, followed by cs.CV, cs.SI, and cs.CL.
